MonitoringLocationName: S Fk Purgatoire - S. Fk. of Purg @ Firestation

MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Greene Street (also State Hwy 110) within the town Silverton, turn southeast onto 14th St and proceed to second bridge.

Traveling on Hwy 550 north descending down the last switch back and hill towards Silverton, take the first right off of 550 onto dirt road about 1/4 mile before 550 and State Hwy 110 split and just before the 550 Hwy Br over Mineral Creek--proceed about 1/10 mile to gauge on Mineral Cr look to your left.
From the town of Bayfield, travel approx 14 mi north on Vallecito Rd (county Rd 501) to FR 603.  Turn right and follow 603 about 5 mi to bridge over Los Pinos River.
From junction of state hwys 151 & 172 in town of Ignacio, travel approx 1/4 mi east on 151 to bridge over Los Pinos River.

From town of Rollinsville, travel approx 0.6 mi south on state hwy 119 to county Rd 15.  Turn right, continue 1/4 mi, and park (just before road forks).  Station is on Gamble Gulch, about 50 ft south of road.
From the town of Crested Butte, travel north approx 3/4 mi on Gothic Rd to bridge over Slate River, just before cemetery.
From the town of Almont, travel south about 3/4 mi on state hwy 135 to Almont Campground.  Station is on Gunnison River, east side of campground.
From state hwy 135 in the town of Almont, take Taylor Canyon Rd east to first bridge
State hwy 135 bridge over East River in town of Almont.
From town of Creede, travel approx 1 mi on northbound state hwy 149 to county Rd 806 (Deep Cr Rd).  Follow 806 about 0.9 mi south to bridge over Rio Grande.
From the town of Del Norte, take US Hwy 160 west approx 5.5 mi, turn right onto Hanna Lane (Rd 17).  Continue 3/4 mi to bridge over Rio Grande.
From junction of US Hwy 160 & state hwy 112 in the town of Del Norte, travel north on 112 approx 1/2 mi to bridge over Rio Grande.
From junction of US Hwys 160 & 285 in the town Monte Vista, travel 2 mi north on 285 to bridge over Rio Grande.
From the town of Delta, travel N on Hwy 50 to the street that goes to Confluence Pk on the N end of town past the City Market lot, once in the Park, walk to the Conf of Unc and Gunn, sample Unc abv
N side of bridge of W Willow Cr, up from the conf with E Willow Cr.  Close to the old Willow Creek Sampling location WW-A.
From the town of Atwood, travel approx 1/4 mi south on state hwy 63 to bridge over S Platte.

MonitoringLocationName: Ten Mile Cr - Bridge Blw Main St
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Exit I-70 onto Main street, Frisco. Left on Forest Drive, park in lot on left, walk to bridge over Tenmile Creek. Sample here.

From west side of the city Brighton, travel west on state hwy 7 (E 160th Ave) 1/2 mi to Veteran's Park.  From Veteran's Park, walk west on path to river, then continue south approx 200 yds (passing under and beyond bridge) to site.
From intersection of US Hwy 85 & state hwy 75 in the city of Littleton, travel approx 1/4 mi west on 75 to bridge over S Platte.

MonitoringLocationName: Clear Cr - Clear Cr Canyon Park
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From station 221 travel 1/2 mile upstream, sample below flow return.

From C-470 and Wadsworth. Take Wadsworth (C-121) South past Chatfield State Park. Turn left on Waterton Canyon Rd and go past Kassler Water Treatment plant.  Site is on West side of Bridge going over South Platte just past treatment plant.

MonitoringLocationName: Lake Fork - San Juan Dr Br
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Driving Directions: Head north on hwy 149 out of Lake City, take a right on dirt road across from Toy Wash into San Juan Ranch Estates. Park at the bridge, sample on bank downstream of bridge.
From town of Delta, travel 2.4 mi east on state hwy 92 to bridge over Gunnison River.- moved 0.2 miles downstream near town of Austin at bridge over 2200 Road, collect SE side of bridge

MonitoringLocationName: N Fk Gunnison - At Hwy 92  Br
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From state hwy 92 within the town of Hotchkiss, turn south on B Street and proceed approx 1/2 mi to bridge.

From the town of Buena Vista travel north on US Hwy 24 approx 8 mi.  Turn east on CR 371 (Look for the Otero Pump Station sign) to bridge over Arkansas River; sample on east side of the river, just upstream from bridge.

MonitoringLocationName: James Cr - Above Left Hand Creek
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From city of Boulder, go north 4.6 mi on US Hwy 36 to Left Hand Canyon Rd; turn west and continue 5.2 miles to James Cr/Left Hand Cr confluence.  Sample James Cr east of bridge, just before mouth.
From junction of US Hwys 24 & 285 south of Buena Vista, travel east approx 1 mi to bridge over Arkansas River.  Station is about 25 yards north of bridge on west bank.

Take Hwy 82 from Glenwood Spgs to Aspen (approx. 50 miles) Take Castle Creek exit, 2nd route in round-a-bout. Take Castle Creek Rd up about 1/4 mile. Turn left at Music School Rd.  Follow road (like a driveway) over the bridge.

MonitoringLocationName: Red Mtn Cr - Abv Uncompahgre Conf on Red Mtn Cr
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Travel South on Hwy 550 to Silverton, after pass CR17 to Mineral Cr (4WD) and the Unc R, travel to first switch back, pull out on left has grave tomb of Hwy worker, sample on other side of road, pull over, Red Mtn Cr
Traveling north on Greene St (also State Hwy 110) in Silverton turn left at the San Juan County Historical Society Museum (end of town just about), sample upstream of bridge.

From I-25 and Hwy 24 in Colorado Springs, travel west on Hwy 24. Turn south (left) on 26th street to intersection of Gold Camp Road. Here 26th becomes Bear Creek Road. Continue on Bear Creek road to point where road ends. A paved road continues at an extreme left. This is Gold Camp Road. At this intersection follow gravel road south. This is High Drive. Park here. Walk approximately 100 yards up High Drive to trail head. You can see USGS station from here. Sample at gauging station.

MonitoringLocationName: Lincoln Cr - Blw Grizzly Res LC3
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From the intersection of CO Hwy 82 and Lincoln Creek Rd (USFS Rd 102) go roughly 5.75 miles up Lincoln Creek Rd. There is a small clump of coniferous trees on the south side of the road where you can pull off. You can access the creek by heading about 100 meters SE down the hill. Roughly 250 feet downstream of the dam.

Beginning at intersection I-25 and US Hwy 24 in Colorado Springs, Trave west on Hwy 24 to intersection of US Hwy 24 and Pikes Peak Hwy at Cascade.  This intersections has a traffic light.  Turn left on to the Pikes Peak Highway and travel approximately 1.5 miles to the toll gate.  From teh toll gate travel along the Pikes Peak Hwy for about one mile to a gate on the left labeled Severy Creek Road. This gate is locked and requires both permission and key to pass (check w/ DOW).

MonitoringLocationName: Lincoln Cr - Blw NY Cr LC1
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From the intersection of CO Hwy 82 and Lincoln Creek Rd (USFS Rd 102) go roughly 1.7 miles up Lincoln Creek Rd. There is a pull out on the right that looks like a campsite but is not a camping area. Sample was collected at this location on Lincoln Creek.

MonitoringLocationName: Lincoln Cr - Blw Truro Cr Conf LC4
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Portal Campground (~0.45 miles from Grizzly Reservoir dam) continue up Lincoln Creek Rd (USFS Rd 102) for approximately 1.17 miles. There are camp sites on either side of the road that you can park at. The station is about 50-70 feet to the west.

From Portal Campground (~0.45 miles from Grizzly Reservoir dam) continue up Lincoln Creek Rd (USFS Rd 102) for approximately 3.37 miles. You will come to a split in the road, go right towards Anderson and Petroleum Lakes trailhead. Cross the stream and you will find parking for the trailhead. Park here and then head roughly 100 feet east down to the stream.

Drive south on Hwy 24 about 4.1 miles from the I-70/Hwy 24 junction, through Minturn (toward Leadville) to a point just north of the Two Elk/Eagle River confluence.  On the river side of the road are several cottonwood trees and space to park a vehicle.  This location is about 200 to 300 feet north of the effluent pipe from the Eagle Mine waste water treatment plant.

Drive south about 3.1 miles from the I-70/Hwy 24 jct on Hwy 24 through Minturn (toward Leadville). At this distance, look for paved rd on left (east) side of rd leading to the river.  Gate across this rd about 50' from the hwy.  Walk though gate to end of rd, turn right and walk another 150-200' to break in old barb wire fence on the left (east). The sample site is down the slope at the river's edge.
From the town of Minturn, travel northwest approx 1.5 mi on US Hwy 24 to a small road crossing the Eagle River.  Sample under bridge of the small road.

From Hwy 50, heading west, drive to 9th Street.  Turn South. Go over bridge, turn left on Sell Ave. ~.4 mi.  Park at River Walk parking lot.  Walk East on trail ~.15 mi to first handicap parking.  Look upstream and you will see drainage culvert on the North side of the bank.

As you come into town (driving from Delta South to North), turn right on S.E Independence Avenue (right after gas station).  The high school is located at the end of this avenue.  You will cross Surface Creek en route.  The easiest way to get to the station will be a left turn (North) on Stonebrook Drive.  Travel approx 0.25 miles until you reach Sandstone Ct (east side of street) which is undeveloped and right next to the high school.  The station will be located directly West of Sandstone Ct. (through the trees to the creek).  There is a green drain pipe that crosses the path next to the creek.

MonitoringLocationName: Dallas Cr - CR 24 Blw Pleasant V Cr
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Ridgeway, W on HWY 62, turn R on CR 24 (Loghill), N on CR 24 at T go left, turn left at next intersection stay on CR24, go S pass a barn on right, stop at Bridge beyond, sample upstream (W) side.  This CR24 crossing is #2 of 4 and below Pleasant Valley Cr

MonitoringLocationName: Lincoln Cr - Ruby Mine adit Runoff S2
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From LC6 and the end of Lincoln Creek Rd (USFS Rd 102) head back down the road towards Grizzly Reservoir for approximately 0.2 miles where you will find mine drainage running across the road. About 150 feet down the road you will find another stream of mine runoff flowing across the road, the collection site is directly upstream from the road.

MonitoringLocationName: Lincoln Cr - Grizzly Res E Shore Abv Diversion GR2
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Roughly 0.1 miles from Grizzly Reservoir dam the road will split, left continues up Lincoln Creek Rd (USFS Rd 102) but stay right and go thru the gate (which says private). You will end up in an equipment parking lot where you should be able to identify a path that terminates in the reservoir where it appears a hatchery truck could easily back up to in order to stock fish.
From the west side of Canon City, travel west 8 mi on US Hwy 50 to bridge crossing the Arkansas River.  Sample at gaging station on north side of bridge.

MonitoringLocationName: La Plata - Abv Long Hollow Cr
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Travel S on Hwy 140 from Durango off Hwy 160 some 20 mi, S on Hwy 141 another 15 mi, when Cr crosses Hwy sample W of hwy

From Hwy 62 & 550 in Ridgeway, travel 8.1 mi N on 550 to the Pa Co Chu Puk Ridgeway St Pk entrance. Turn left, follow rd to Loop G campgrd, Park at N end, walk N to picnic shelter, turn left to trail NW to river, walk to river, turn right Cow Cr and go upstream 30 yds to where not braided, sample
behind the Angler's Covey store across from S 20th Street
In Salida, on Hwy 50, find State St, go across the street, SW Conservation Corp and hotel and river is behind those buildings, Ecosystems Learning Center is building a bridge and meeting area there

MonitoringLocationName: Spring Cr - Bridge at Lesher MS
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Lesher Middle School in Fort Collins, turn right on Prospect off of Stover St.Turn left immediately on Stover street to the south. Go approximately 2 blocks to the bridge over Spring Creek. The sample site is just below the bridge on the downstream side of the bridge.

From the junction of HWY 160/550 in Durango, travel north on 550 (Main Avenue) to 15th St.  Turn right, then left at the rail road tracks.  Continue through Rotary Park to pedestrian bridge over the Animas River.

From the junction of 160/550 in Durango, travel north on 550 (Main Avenue) to 32nd St.  Turn Right onto 32nd St.  Proceed across the bridge and turn Left onto River Bend Rd.  Sample upstream of the bridge.
Travel North on HWY 550 to Silverton, take the first right off of 550 just before the 550/110 split and town (dirt road).  Travel about five tenths of a mile up and sample.

Travel north on HWY 550 towards Ouray.  Turn right off of 550 onto Ouray CR 20D--Ironton Park.  Follow the dirt road along the river for about three tenths of a mile to the inlet circle part of the road.
Travel north on HWY 550 towards Ouray.  Turn right onto Engineer Mountain Road (Ouray CR 18), sample right above where the river goes under the highway.

Travel north on HWY 550 to Ouray.  Turn left on 7th Avenue and then right on Ouray CR 17.  Proceed down CR 17 to the USGS Gauge (there is a pedestrian bridge right by it and you can see HWY 550 from the site). Station is to your right, on Uncompahgre River.

Travel south on HWY 550/160 to the La Plata County Humane Society on the right side of the road right after  crossing the 550/160 bridge and where HWY 3 splits off to the left.  Drive down the dirt road to the river.

MonitoringLocationName: E Mancos - E. Mancos at Samson Diversion
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From E of Mancos on Hwy 160, take Rd 44 to Echo Basin. Turn R on RD L .Turn R at 1st driveway on right. Park at Brown family cabin.  Samson diversion located S of Brown family cabin.

MonitoringLocationName: Middle Mancos - Mid Mancos Abv Conf Mancos at Rd L
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From E of Mancos on Hwy 160, take Rd 44 to Echo Basin. Turn R on RD L heading W approx. 0.3 miles. Middle Mancos intersects RD L. Sample site is on the L side of the road

MonitoringLocationName: Mancos - Mid Mancos At Viets Diversion
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Heading W on CO HWY 160 Business from Mancos, turn L approx. 0.2 miles past Western Excelsior plant entrance onto access road. Follow access road approx. 0.4 to the end at Viets Diversion headgate. Cross fence to the S to river and the sample site.
Heading W on CO HWY 160 from Mancos, turn L on RD 39. Turn L into second driveway (Alexander property-8748 RD 39).  Site is located approx. 45 yds S of driveway on the E side of bridge.
Heading W on CO HWY 160 from Mancos, turn L on RD 38. Go approx. 2 miles then turn L at RD F. Sample site is on S side of RD F bridge.

MonitoringLocationName: Mud Cr - Mud Creek Abv conf Mancos at Rds 37/38
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Heading W on CO HWY 160 from Mancos, turn L on RD 38. Travel approx. 2.5 miles to intersect of RD 38 and 37 (gravel road open seasonally). Sample site is 200 ft. E of intersection.
3.7 miles south of the light Hwy 550 at Ridgeway, is turnoff for Potter's Ranch. Turn west off of Hwy 550 onto CR 3A and travel about 1/2 mile to bridge.  Sample upstream side of bridge.

16.5 miles north of Ouray on Hwy 550. Turn at Paco Chu Puck State Pk below Ridgeway Reservoir. Travel on One way park rd to first left or sign saying picnic/walk area (continuing straight takes you to restrooms), follow road down past fish cleaning station to walking bridge (only one).  Sometimes gates are open and you can drive closer than other times.

From the intersection of Highways 550 and 62 in Ridgway, CO, travel about 2.4 miles north on Hwy 550 to the junction with CR24. Turn left onto CR24, then in less than 0.1 mile turn right into a trailhead parking area. Sampling site is on the upstream side of the CR24 bridge.

MonitoringLocationName: M Fk S Platte - Fairplay Beach
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From South Park HS: Follow 6th St SW for 2 blocks to Front Street. Take the metal staircase down behind Hand Hotel to Fairplay Beach. Walk SW across the damn and follow path to pedistrian bridge. Sample below the bridge.

From the intersection of Highways 550 and 62 in Ridgway, CO, travel about 0.3 mile west on Hwy 62 to Railroad St. Turn right (north) onto N. Railroad St and travel about 0.35 mile. Turn right into a gravel parking area. Procede to the far south end of the parking area. Sampling site is reached via a path angling southeast to the river; just upstream of a submerged log.
Below trib 4, Heading from Telluride to Ophir, take low raod in E Ophir to end of road, Go down to bridge across creek to sample
From junction of US Hwy 160 & state hwy 184 in town of Mancos, travel 3 blks west on 160 to Beech St.  Turn left and follow Beech 0.3 mi south to bridge over Mancos River.
From Telluride head to Ophir, in Ophir stop at Harley Brooke Hitching Driveway. Fence w/ flag 1.5 mi W of Ophir, take driveway to stream
CJ's bridge
South of Durango, CO  downstream of Sante Rita Park, below pumping plant
From Telluride head to Ophir, on Ophir Rd- go on up to pass, Rd E of E Ophir about 1/4 mi, to Carbonero Tailings access Rd, bushwak from powerline to river
From Telluride head to Ophir, just before Ophir, about 1 mi before, stream is there, sample upstram from ford
Fr Hwy 36 (28th St) in Boulder, turn E on Arapahoe Rd and then S on 30th St.  Turn rt into Scott Carpenter Park.  Walk to cr -- site is bet the ped br and the bike path underpass.
Ophir DW source
Head towards Ophir from Telluride, on right on Ophir access Rd about 1 mi, before town, cross creek and walk to draining adit
Drive to Ophir, CO. Hike up to Waterfall Canyon water system uptake, canyon is south of old , west Ophir

From the intersection of hwy 24 and hwy 67 in Woodland Park, travel north approximately 8 miles. Turn right on CR79 for 0.1 mile to parking lot. Sample site is on trout creek, upstream side of CR-79 culvert.
From Betty Ford Alpine Center, follow Betty Ford Way towards Gore Cr to walking path, then walk down path to Gore Cr
From town of Norwood, travel approx 5 mi east on state hwy 145 to bridge over San Miguel River.

MonitoringLocationName: Short Draw - Abv Conf N Fk Gunnison
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Bridge St in Hotchkiss, turn S on 3rd and just before street ends there is a walking path to fairgrounds on E side.  Sampling site is where path crosses Short Draw - from bridge or just downstream.
Go to Cold Harbor Institute in Gunnison, Colorado , once on the property, head west to the edge and sample at the meander where the river turns north after flowing west by the west property boundary

At Glenwood Spgs exit off I-70, turn right at the traffic light (onto 6th St).  Then turn right at Grand Ave, right at 8th St, right on Colorado Ave, and left on 7th St.  Follow 7th approx 1/4 mi to bridge over Roaring Fork River.

MonitoringLocationName: W Monument C - Air Force Acad
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From junction of I-25 & US Hwy 85/87 (Nevada Ave) in the city of Colorado Spgs, travel north approx 2.5 mi on I-25 to South Gate Blvd.  Follow South Gate northwest another 2.5 mi to Stadium Dr and turn left.  After road curves to the right and becomes Pine Dr, take first left and proceed to Air Acad HS.  Walk south from HS to nature trail, follow this trail to stream.

At Glenwood Spgs exit off I-70, turn right at the traffic light (onto 6th St).  Then turn right at Grand Ave, left at 8th St, left at Cooper Ave, left at 7th St; then immediately park.  Station is at base of pedestrian bridge just to the north.

Fr Hwy 160 at Hwy 550 in DGO, travel W on 160 approx 1.7 miles, turn rt in Twin Buttes dev.  Take 1st left into Animas HS complex and park.  Walk W to far side of westmost bldg along river trl.  At approx 150' the trail begins up the hill to the rt, but continue along cr for approx 50' until metal fence line of left ends.
Take Hwy 586 S from Howardsville and site is located just below the gauge which is below confluence of Cunningham Cr, and a little below the cabin built on the edge of the avalanch zone from Brendel
From town of Weston, travel approx 10 mi west on state hwy 12 to county Rd 13.  Turn south onto 13 and proceed to first bridge.
From town of Weston, travel approx 3.2 mi east on state hwy 12 to Primero HS.  Station is on Purgatoire River, behind school.

From Poncha Springs, head S on Hwy 285 towards Poncha Pass.  After crossing bridge over S Fk Arkansas, go .60 miles to where CR 206 intersects on right side of hwy.  On left side, across from CR 206, is a pull off that leads down to a picnic area.  Park here and walk down to footbridge -- site is on upstream side.
From junction of US Hwys 50 & 287 within town of Lamar, travel 1.2 mi north on 50/287 to bridge over Arkansas River.
From the town of Aspen, travel approx 9.7 mi southeast on state hwy 82 to Lincoln Gulch Campground.  Station is in campground, on Lincoln Cr.
Fr I-25 nr Trinidad, take exit 14B and go W on Hwy 12 (Hwy of Legends).  Go L at CR 18.3 and follow to T (Fedora Dr).  Go L approx 100 m to parking area on right.  Park and walk to creek.
From US Hwy 36 and Hwy N Foothills intersection go west on 36 to McConnel, turn left and sample upstream of Br

MonitoringLocationName: Fountain Cr - MS1 - Abv Garden Gods Rd
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From CO Spgs, take US-24 W to Manitou Spgs.  Exit US-24 BUS exit.  Keep R at fork and follow signs for US-24 BUS.  Merge onto Manitou Ave and go to Manitou Pool and Fitness Center parking lot.
From Kremmling, head E on Hwy 40 approx 5.36 miles to CR39.  Go S approx .77 miles to bridge over Colorado River.  Sample from bridge.
From I-25 Exit 14, Mulberry Avenue and go west, turn S on Timberline, Survey N of Bridge

From intersection of I-25 & state hwy 14 (Mulberry St) near city of Ft Collins, travel 7 mi west on Mulberry St to Overland Trail Rd.  Turn right and follow Overland Tr Rd approx 3 mi, then turn left into Lyons Park.  Station is on Cache La Poudre River, next to parking lot.

In Pagosa Springs, from the intersection of Hwy 160 and Hot Springs Blvd, travel south on Hot Springs Blvd. Turn West (right) on Apache st. After crossing the bridge, turn south (left on S 5th st. Park at Yamaguchi Park. Walk to the NW corner of the park. Sample upstream of the man-made wave feature.
To reach station from within the city of Aurora, travel north on Peoria St. to the Sand Cr. Park turnoff (A right turn at the 2400 block.)  Park and walk on path down hill to Sand Cr.
From state hwy 13/789 in town of Meeker, turn south onto 5th St and proceed just over 1 block to bridge crossing White River.

From the junction of US Hwys 50 & 550 in the town of Montrose, take 550 southeast to Colorado Ave (across from S 9th St).  Turn right, then left at Rio Grande Ave, right at Apollo.  Follow Apollo to River Bottom Park, station is at footbridge in park.
6.5 mi SW from La Veta on Hwy 12, left bank at Boyd Ranch, guage, Spoon Ranch

MonitoringLocationName: Left Hand Cr - Left Hand Cr at Peak to Peak
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From the jct of Hwy 72 and Lefthand Canyon Dr in Ward, travel south 1.04 miles on Hwy 72 (MM43).  Site on creek just upstream from Hwy72, between old stone bridge and a culvert running under hwy.

MonitoringLocationName: Left Hand Cr - Left Hand Cr at California G
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Ward, travel 1.3 miles south on Lefthand Canyon Dr to the jct with California Gulch Rd and Sawmill Rd.  Next, go 0.3 mile NW on California Gulch Rd.  Site is on creek immediately west of the road.

MonitoringLocationName: S Fk Clear Cr - S Fk Clear Cr in Georgetown

MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Georgetown, take Guanella Pass Rd to Silverdale Trailhead. Sampling point on Leavenoworth creek above south fork clear creek.

MonitoringLocationName: S Fk Clear Cr - Above Leavenworth
East Fork of Dallas Creek - Below Conf. of Blue Lk and E Dallas Cr
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From the junction of Highways 550 and 62 in Ridgway, CO, take Highway 62 west to Ouray County Road 7 (CR7), about 4.8 miles. Turn left (south) on CR7 and follow it to the Blue Lakes trailhead parking area, a little over 7 miles. On foot, take the Blue Lakes trail to Lower Blue Lake. At the point where the trail continuing to Upper Blue Lake crosses the Lower Blue Lake outlet stream, turn left (north) and follow E. Dallas Cr downstream about 400 ft to the River Watch sampling site.

MonitoringLocationName: Little James Cr - Above Yellow Girl
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Jamestown, take James Canyon Drive 0.5 miles. Sample location on right, marked with flags.

Head west on the frontage rd southwest of the Golden Fwy (CO 58) and McIntyre St intersection. About 100 yards down there is a pull off in front of the gate to get into Coors property. The water is 50 feet south from there.

MonitoringLocationName: Government Draw - Abv Long Hollow Res

MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From I-25 near the city of Fort Collins, depart at Exit 268 (Prospect Rd).  Travel 5 mi west on Prospect to Shields St.  Turn left and proceed approx 1/3 mi to bridge over Spring Cr.
From I-25 near the city of Fort Collins, depart at Exit 268 (Prospect Rd).  Travel approx 1.4 mi west on Prospect to bridge over Cache La Poudre River.

MonitoringLocationName: Long Hollow Cr - Abv Long Hollow Res

MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Routt Cty Courthouse on 5th street: Cross Lincoln Ave heading toward Rodeo grounds. Either cross 5th St Br and park at Howesen or turn right on Yampa Ave before the bridge and park on Yampa Ave. The site is upstream of bridge.

MonitoringLocationName: Brush Cr - Sylvan Lake Road Br
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Starting from US6 and Sylvan Lake Rd roundabout in Eagle, head SW for 1.5 miles. Once you cross the bridge over Brush Cr, park on the north (left) side of the road. Walk down the hill along the bridge and through the willows on the trail to reach the sampling point.

From Intersection of I-25 & US Hwy 24 in the city of Colorado Springs, travel about 3/4 mi east on Hwy 24, turn right at Nevada Ave.  Continue approx 1.25 mi to Cheyenne Rd (NOT Cheyenne Blvd), turn right and travel 1.5 mi to Canon Elem.  Station is directly behind school.
From I-25 in the city of Denver, exit northbound on University Blvd and proceed approx 2 mi to bridge over Cherry Cr. Sta moved closer to park in 2017

From US6 and Sylvan Lake Rd roundabout in Eagle, head SW for 1.6 miles. Turn right onto Brush Cr Rd and travel 1.7 miles. The destination will be on the right. Park in gravel lot and walk south toward river.

From US6 and Sylvan Lake Rd roundabout in Eagle, head SW for 1.6 miles. Turn right onto Brush Cr Rd and travel 2.8 miles. Turn left into Brush Cr Valley Ranch Open Space parking lot. Walk north on trail toward bridge for sampling.

From US6 and Sylvan Lake Rd roundabout in Eagle, head SW for 1.6 miles. Turn right onto Brush Cr Rd and travel 8.6 miles. Park on the right shoulder in front of the Sylvan Lake State Park sign, across from visitor center entrance. Walk down the embankment and cross old road to reach sampling site.

MonitoringLocationName: Razor Cr - Razor above Vouga Res
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Gunnison, travel 19.3 miles to Doyleville and take a right on Gunnison CR-45, becomes Saguache CR-14PP. Take CR W18 on Razor Creek Ranch (Private - Get permission). and work to pasture above reservoir and walk up to sampling site.  Non Private Route: BLM road 3184 to two rack to right which heads up to Vouga Reservoir. Continue around reservoir and upstream until you reach fence line and sampling site. Rough road - consider UTV.

MonitoringLocationName: Left Hand Cr - Above James Cr
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From city of Boulder, go north 4.6 mi on US Hwy 36 to Left Hand Canyon Rd; turn west and follow Left Hand Canyon Rd 5.8 miles to a point where road crosses Left Hand Cr (0.6 mi upstream from James Cr/Left Hand Cr confluence).
From city of Boulder, go north 3.3 mi on US Hwy 36 to county Rd 26.  Turn right and follow 26 approx 1.3 mi to 41st St.  Make the mandatory left turn and proceed to first bridge.

From Gunnison, travel 19.3 miles to Doyleville and take a right on Gunnison County Road 45 (Doyleville cutoff). After crossing valley (1mile), take left on county road 46 and continue, following signs to needle creek reservoir. Continue around Needle Creek Reservoir (Saguache CR-25TT and continue up road on needle creek. Continue until you drop over divide in Razor Creek at Razor Creek Park. Road is narrow and steep but passible with full sized pickup. UTV may be faster.

MonitoringLocationName: Wahatoya Cr - Wahatoya Cr at MM 6.1
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From the corner of Birch and Cascade in LaVeta, travel down CR 360 for 6.1 miles to the bridge that crosses Wahatoya Creek. This is the testing site.
Go 1/2 mile North of Paonia State Park entrance on Hwy 133.  Look for turnoff on East side of Hwy before confluence of the East and West of Muddy. Sample here
Sample just below the Fire Mountain irrigation diversion located along Hwy 133, west of the town of Somerset. Irrigation diversion structure is visible from the road.

Turn off to Pleasure Park off of Hwy 133 approx 5 miles west of the town of Hotchkisss. At the bottom of the road, turn left into the BLM parking area, NOT the commercial Pleasure Park area. Trails lead to the river, sample above the confluence with the Gunnison.

Directions to site:  From the intersection of 6th Avenue and Highway 550 in Ouray, CO, take 550 south about 10.1 miles. On the map below, the River Watch site is at the site labeled RM-05 at a wide shoulder on the right (west) side of 550. The Commodore Gulch stream passes under US 550. The sample site would be on the upstream side of the highway. [Note that the RW sampling site is the same as CDPHE WQCD site RM-05, named ??Commodore Gulch at US Highway 550?g].

The River Watch sampling site is at the blue marker (GC-05) slightly upstream of the road. [Note that the RW sampling site is the same as Site UWP-GC-05, named Gray Copper Gulch Mouth].

[Note that the RW sampling site is the same as CDPHE WQCD site RM-02, named ??Red Mtn Creek abv Idarado near MM81?g].

From US Highway 24 turn to take Elbert Road Northbound for 5.2 miles, turn right on Sweet Road for 2.3 miles, turn left on Gollihar Road for 0.8 miles to the regional park parking lot.

From the town of Woody Creek, intersection of Hwy 82 and Snowmass Cr Rd, head north on county road 17.  Follow Rd 17 approx 3.3 mi to bridge over Roaring Fk River. Park in parking area on far side of bridge adn take sample from bridge.
Samples are taken from the bridge on Emma Rd. within the town of Basalt.  (The bridge crossing the Roaring Fk. River.)

Starting from C72 and C93, head North on 93. Turn right on 72. Turn left onto Hallett st. At the round about go right onto 94th Ave. At the pedestrian sign at flattop intersection go left. The creek is down to the right on Flattop st.
From intersection of state hwy 86 & county Rd 13 at west edge of the town Elizabeth, travel approx 3.2 mi north to Running Brook Rd.  Turn right and proceed 1/4 mi to Running Creek.
From downtown Basalt, travel east on Midland Ave; take first major right turn onto the Pueblo Bridge over the Frying Pan River.

MonitoringLocationName: Lk Fk Gunnison - Abv Henson Cr

MonitoringLocationName: Henson Cr - Abv Lk Fk Gunn
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From Hwy 149 and 2nd in Lake City, head across the Henson Cr bridgeand make an immediate rt into RV park.  Sample from upstream bank.

From the intersection of Hwy 82 and Snowmass Cr Rd, drive 7.3 miles. Make a left onto Woods Rd (Crossing over Northbound lane of Hwy 82), make immediate Right onto private property (House #34425), Drive to house,  park, go down to gate on southeast side of property, down to creek and sample.

From intersection of Hwy 82 and Snowmass Cr Rd, take a right at light up Snowmass Cr Rd and travel 1.6 miles to small overpass that crosses Capitol Cr, park car and take sample from bridge or perperty (house with stilts) just upstream from bridge.

Sampling location is immediately at exit of culvert.

Park, walk downstrm toward telepole and phone box, then follow trail down towards stream, go straight, not on switchbacks, to creek and sample in willow grove.

From Hwy 82 in Gldwood Spgs go W on 27th St until it crosses Roaring Fk and becomes Midland Ave.  About 1.5 mi from Hwy 82 turn right at stop sign to 4mi Rd, CR117.  Go about 9 mi b4 resort, turn right on FR300, Fourmile Pk. About 2.2 mi rd crosses Cr. Just past this, park and walk back, a narrow path on N side of Cr, upstrm of rd, left bank and site
North side of Clear Creek Trail along West Lake. Sample on Clear Creek 0.1 miles downstream of the overpass.

From town of Oak Creek, travel approx 1.25 mi south on state hwy 131 to county Rd 14.  Turn left and continue 5.6 mi to county Rd 18.  Turn right and proceed 2 miles (to a point about 1/4 mi beyond Stagecoach Res Dam); station is to your right, on Yampa River.

This site is best accessed starting at the Dahlia Trailhead along the Colorado Front Range Trail/Sand Creek Regional Greenway trail. The trail is located on the southern side of the Dahlia Trailhead parking lot. After parking at the trailhead, one must either reach the destination by bike or walking. Once on the trail, turn right and continue heading northwest along the concrete trail for approximately 1.3 miles. The sampling site is located on the left within Sand Creek, where Suncor's effluent pipe is present across the river. Sampling occurs just downstream where effluent drains into Sand Creek. This site is located less than 0.5 miles upstream from Sand Creek?uus confluence with the South Platte River.

From Basalt, S on Hwy 82 towards Aspen. Turn R or W on Brush Cr Rd heading to Snowmass V. Go 2.5 mi to roundabout, then go S on Highline Rd. Go about 0.5 mi, turn R or W onto Snowmass Club Circle. Cross Br and immd turn R or N on Clubhouse Dr. Go about 0.1 mi to br over Brush Cr. Sample  about 100 yds dwnstrm of Clubhouse Dr Br. Follow footpath from br, will cross cr and just beyond is site, 30ft blw WWTEffluent, a noticeable pipe.
Upstream of bridge crossing on CR360, go south on CO360 out of La Veta. Site is near cabins on left side of road.
